https://git-scm.com/book/ch2-5.html


navigate to the desired directory

cd gitexp
git remote add pb https://github.com/nethravathitc/gitexp (pb vl b other name for the URL, by executing this v r saying where is our remote repository)
git init (vl initial ur current directory)
git add file_name
git status (to check the added file for which are about to commit)

git commit -m "comment that you want for ur file"
git push pb master

git clone URL
git pull

git remote -v (to know the name of the configured remote server)
git remote -v (to know the url associated with remote server)

